WEBVTT

00:09.093 --> 00:11.095
[♪♪♪]

00:17.643 --> 00:19.854
♪ Young man goes out ♪

00:20.020 --> 00:25.526
♪ Looking for the diamond in the sea ♪

00:28.529 --> 00:32.491
♪ Old man rows his boat to shore ♪

00:32.658 --> 00:36.161
♪ And falls on twisted knee ♪

00:38.831 --> 00:45.797
♪ And you'll drown
Before the water lets you in ♪

00:48.007 --> 00:54.973
♪ And you'll you drown
Before the water lets you in ♪♪

01:27.129 --> 01:29.381
[Potts on recording]
Can you say your name for the record?

01:29.966 --> 01:31.091
[young John]
John Rayburn.

01:31.759 --> 01:35.387
- [Potts] How old are you, John?
- [young John] Fourteen.

01:38.265 --> 01:40.768
[Potts] You understand
you're not in any trouble?

01:46.691 --> 01:47.942
Yes, sir.

01:48.150 --> 01:51.988
[Potts] I just want to know the truth
about what happened with your brother.

01:53.155 --> 01:54.156
Yes, sir.

01:55.449 --> 01:56.993
[Potts]
And what happened?

01:58.619 --> 02:00.538
[young John]
He was hit by a car.

02:06.335 --> 02:08.379
[Potts]
And was your father there?

02:10.673 --> 02:12.174
[young John]
No, sir.

02:12.383 --> 02:15.887
He was at the hospital with my sister.

02:19.431 --> 02:20.892
[sighs]

02:32.028 --> 02:33.905
Play it again.

02:36.574 --> 02:37.742
[Danny sighs]

02:39.493 --> 02:41.203
[cell phone ringing]

02:48.127 --> 02:49.420
[scoffs]

02:53.925 --> 02:56.677
Hey, I was just thinking about you.

02:56.886 --> 02:58.429
Really?

02:59.055 --> 03:00.973
No, I was.

03:01.640 --> 03:03.851
Is there some kind of problem?

03:04.727 --> 03:06.687
No.

03:08.898 --> 03:12.651
I was just wondering
how you're doing, that's all.

03:12.860 --> 03:15.821
I didn't talk to you after the service.

03:18.116 --> 03:20.325
Was there
something you wanted to say?

03:21.535 --> 03:23.913
No. I just...

03:25.372 --> 03:27.833
Just wanted
to see how you were doing.

03:29.085 --> 03:31.545
Oh, yeah. I'm great, John.

03:31.963 --> 03:33.005
[clicks]

03:34.506 --> 03:35.841
What was that?

03:36.050 --> 03:40.387
Oh, that was just the sound of me
cocking a pistol, putting it to my head.

03:42.681 --> 03:44.516
Don't fucking joke
around with me, Danny.

03:45.059 --> 03:47.103
Don't fuck around with me like this.

03:47.311 --> 03:49.396
That was a joke, right?

03:49.981 --> 03:52.817
Yeah, John. It was a joke.

04:01.700 --> 04:04.369
Hey, how'd you like
to go fishing this weekend?

04:06.747 --> 04:09.959
- Fishing?
- Yeah, fishing.

04:15.631 --> 04:17.008
Danny.

04:25.057 --> 04:27.101
I'm busy this weekend.

04:32.148 --> 04:34.150
[♪♪♪]

05:51.685 --> 05:53.187
[breathes sharply]

06:12.248 --> 06:14.166
[cell phone ringing]

06:17.669 --> 06:20.422
- This is Lenny.
- [John] Hey, it's John Rayburn.

06:20.631 --> 06:21.632
Hey, John.

06:21.840 --> 06:23.801
Listen, I was wondering
if you had a chance

06:23.884 --> 06:25.136
maybe we could speak?

06:25.344 --> 06:28.264
Well, I'm getting ready
to go out and bag a few bonefish.

06:28.472 --> 06:31.516
Oh, I'm sorry.
I thought you'd left by now.

06:31.725 --> 06:35.229
I was going to.
I thought, what the heck,

06:35.437 --> 06:40.567
I doubt if I'll be down this way again,
I might as well enjoy myself.

06:41.401 --> 06:43.279
Hey, I'll call you when we get back.

06:43.487 --> 06:48.033
No, that'd be great. I appreciate that.
And listen, good luck out there.

06:48.242 --> 06:51.954
Oh, we don't need no luck.
Bastards don't stand a chance.

07:00.587 --> 07:02.131
[Sally]
Got everything you need?

07:02.506 --> 07:04.216
Have fun.

07:15.811 --> 07:18.063
- Oh, good morning.
- Hey.

07:20.024 --> 07:24.528
Mama, I think I need a couple--
Maybe, just, can I take a break?

07:24.736 --> 07:28.073
Can I--
Just a small break. Couple of days.

07:28.866 --> 07:31.785
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. I just-- I just--

07:31.994 --> 07:36.040
I just-- I think I need a day
just to drive down to Key West.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.916
Take a break, you know?

07:39.668 --> 07:41.420
All right, then.

07:42.296 --> 07:43.714
[sighs]

07:45.465 --> 07:47.509
Enjoy it.

08:10.991 --> 08:14.453
[Eric] Welcome back
to the dark side, my man.

08:14.661 --> 08:17.248
You ready for another gas run?

08:17.915 --> 08:19.333
That's not why I called you.

08:19.583 --> 08:24.004
Huh. Serious? In one night
you'll make, like, I don't know,

08:24.171 --> 08:26.382
six months' worth
what your family pays you.

08:26.506 --> 08:30.052
- I already told you I'm not interested.
- Then what the fuck you doing here?

08:31.178 --> 08:32.554
[Danny]
This is why I called.

08:33.680 --> 08:35.640
Heh. That's what you want?

08:35.849 --> 08:37.435
What? Are you gonna judge me now?

08:38.143 --> 08:39.437
Fuck you.

08:39.644 --> 08:43.023
I don't fucking judge. I just don't
take money from my friends. Okay?

08:44.149 --> 08:46.277
No judging.

08:56.287 --> 08:57.662
[speaks indistinctly]

08:57.829 --> 09:01.125
No, I need more than that.
Gotta get the eight ball rolling.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.752
- Here we go.
- Here you go.

09:03.961 --> 09:06.671
- Take it.
- I'm not taking your fucking money.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.257
Okay?

09:08.466 --> 09:10.550
- Thanks, man.
- All right. You're welcome.

09:10.759 --> 09:14.596
That's a lot of powder
for a party of one.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.140
Who you hanging with?

09:17.099 --> 09:19.935
[chuckles] I'm just saying,
I'm free this evening.

09:20.144 --> 09:23.439
I... have no plans.

09:24.273 --> 09:26.317
Let's go.

09:28.026 --> 09:29.820
Have fun.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.413
Belle?

09:43.792 --> 09:45.877
Babe, you here?

10:24.875 --> 10:26.001
[sighs]

10:47.689 --> 10:49.066
[grunts]

10:53.278 --> 10:54.654
[Sally]
It came today.

10:54.738 --> 10:59.201
Probate court sends a copy to the
surviving spouse. You should look it over.

10:59.410 --> 11:02.996
I did look at it. Danny's been cut out.

11:03.539 --> 11:04.748
Dad didn't tell you?

11:04.956 --> 11:07.084
He tried. I wouldn't listen.

11:07.585 --> 11:10.504
You didn't want to be involved.
You let Dad make decisions.

11:10.712 --> 11:13.757
I know.
It was a mistake. I shouldn't have.

11:17.469 --> 11:19.804
I want you to make this right, Meggy.

11:20.764 --> 11:23.183
Talk to your brothers.

11:29.814 --> 11:31.316
Fuck.

11:32.109 --> 11:34.111
[rock music playing over stereo]

11:56.634 --> 11:58.176
[snorts]

12:08.270 --> 12:10.147
[sniffing]

12:20.658 --> 12:24.495
♪ Come on, jump in ♪

12:24.662 --> 12:29.040
♪ You gotta push yourself again ♪

12:31.669 --> 12:34.463
Can I get a tequila? Tequila.

12:37.341 --> 12:38.967
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

12:40.511 --> 12:44.806
♪ There's no doubt
You're in a rut ♪

12:44.973 --> 12:47.643
♪ You'll find a way out ♪

12:49.227 --> 12:50.729
Can I get another one of those?

12:50.937 --> 12:52.731
Sure.

12:55.108 --> 12:57.068
[tequila pouring]

12:57.235 --> 12:58.778
[glass thumps]

13:00.405 --> 13:02.616
- [Manny] Here you are.
- [Meg] Hey, Manny.

13:02.700 --> 13:04.451
Thank you for bringing it around.

13:04.660 --> 13:06.870
[Manny]
Hey, Ms. Rayburn, can I talk to you?

13:07.078 --> 13:09.247
[Meg]
Sure. What is it?

13:09.456 --> 13:11.583
I have a problem.

13:12.125 --> 13:15.003
Do you think you should talk to Gwen,
or my mom?

13:15.212 --> 13:18.965
No, it's not really about work.
It's for me.

13:19.174 --> 13:22.802
Well, for my cousin Carlos.
You remember him?

13:23.011 --> 13:24.555
Yes, I do.

13:24.763 --> 13:29.100
He liked you. Your family
was always very good to him.

13:30.435 --> 13:32.812
Now he needs...

13:33.772 --> 13:35.148
We need you, Ms. Rayburn.

13:35.357 --> 13:36.608
Me? Why?

13:36.816 --> 13:38.527
He needs a lawyer.

13:40.987 --> 13:43.365
[Kevin] Could you imagine
if he'd come right through here?

13:43.448 --> 13:45.743
- Walked along--
- [Susie] Kevin!

13:45.950 --> 13:49.371
- Got your message, doll.
- Hey, Susie. Excuse me.

13:49.580 --> 13:52.165
So you're doing it.
You're actually leaving us.

13:52.374 --> 13:55.043
Well, my sister's got
a house up in Hendersonville.

13:55.210 --> 13:56.961
I can't do this salt air anymore.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.297
Mom's going
to be brokenhearted without you.

13:59.506 --> 14:03.009
Your mother and father were good
to me after Cliff died.

14:03.093 --> 14:04.261
I'll never forget that.

14:04.469 --> 14:07.514
I know. So listen,
I was talking to your son

14:07.723 --> 14:14.521
and... I was surprised you didn't come
to me first before you decided to sell.

14:15.439 --> 14:17.274
Nicky said he wanted to handle it.

14:17.482 --> 14:19.526
Sue, we have
talked about this for years.

14:20.277 --> 14:23.029
And if you wanted it,
you could have made an offer.

14:23.238 --> 14:25.574
I just assumed you couldn't afford it.

14:25.783 --> 14:29.369
A yacht club? Triple the dock space.
It's going to kill my business.

14:29.578 --> 14:32.163
Kevin, sooner or later
someone else is gonna come in.

14:33.457 --> 14:36.918
First a yacht club, then what?
Condominiums?

14:37.127 --> 14:39.170
This place will look
like Pompano Beach.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.172
They're offering way above market.

14:41.381 --> 14:44.676
Okay, listen, I can't do that.
But what if I pay in cash?

14:46.637 --> 14:49.389
- Cash?
- Please, Sue...

14:49.598 --> 14:52.267
I need this. Please?

14:56.271 --> 14:59.023
If you come up with money
by the end of the month, deal.

14:59.232 --> 15:02.068
I will. I talked to the bank.
Everything's in place.

15:02.152 --> 15:04.070
I promise you, I'll make this work.

15:04.696 --> 15:08.908
I hope you do.
How's Belle doing these days?

15:11.202 --> 15:14.956
- Good. She's good.
- Good. Tell her I said hello.

15:15.165 --> 15:18.627
And before I move, I'm having
the two of you over for dinner.

15:18.836 --> 15:20.920
- Sounds good.
- All right.

15:28.637 --> 15:30.013
What's on your mind?

15:36.269 --> 15:38.897
What's the statute of limitations?

15:39.105 --> 15:40.691
What for?

15:42.400 --> 15:44.569
Giving false statements to the police.

15:48.740 --> 15:52.243
You were kids, and you were scared.

15:52.744 --> 15:55.038
You were all scared.

16:02.170 --> 16:03.296
What happened?

16:04.964 --> 16:07.634
- You know what happened.
- No, I mean...

16:08.968 --> 16:10.554
Your side of it. What happened?

16:13.765 --> 16:17.728
I heard there was a drowning.
Came over the radio.

16:18.019 --> 16:20.355
Didn't know who it was at first.

16:20.689 --> 16:23.692
When I found out
it was your sister who had died,

16:23.859 --> 16:26.778
I went to the hospital
and found your father.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.072
He was there with Danny.

16:29.280 --> 16:34.452
He was having his injuries examined.
I talked to him in the examination room.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.665
You talked to both of them together?

16:40.709 --> 16:44.963
Yes. That was my first mistake.
I should have talked to them separately.

16:45.171 --> 16:50.385
I asked your father what happened,
he said your brother had got hit by a car.

16:51.094 --> 16:54.472
- And when I asked Danny--
- He gave the same story.

16:54.806 --> 16:57.267
Yes. I blew it.

16:57.768 --> 17:00.771
I let Bobby feed him the lie.

17:01.145 --> 17:03.982
But when I pressed Danny afterwards...

17:04.608 --> 17:08.194
he said he didn't remember details.

17:08.653 --> 17:10.948
I knew something was off.

17:11.155 --> 17:13.951
- That's when you came to talk to us.
- Yeah.

17:14.158 --> 17:17.412
You, Kevin, Meg.

17:17.579 --> 17:20.707
Your mother wasn't there.

17:23.251 --> 17:24.878
She was out of town.

17:26.755 --> 17:30.133
I always thought
it was an odd time to take a trip.

17:32.886 --> 17:34.178
Why is that?

17:36.139 --> 17:41.436
Well, you know, she had the inn
to manage, and tourist season coming up.

17:43.146 --> 17:48.276
Anyway, talking to you three,
it became clear

17:48.485 --> 17:51.655
because you
had all told the same story.

17:51.822 --> 17:54.908
Which means that you had been fed
the same lie.

17:55.116 --> 17:57.494
And I never asked who fed you that lie.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.080
I should have pressed it.

18:01.414 --> 18:04.501
But you all were a family in pain.

18:04.709 --> 18:07.211
Bobby was my friend.

18:09.380 --> 18:11.842
I thought it best to let you all grieve.

18:16.095 --> 18:19.474
My dad never
talked to you about any of this?

18:19.683 --> 18:21.643
I confronted him.

18:22.644 --> 18:27.148
Yeah. A few months later.
He kept denying it.

18:28.775 --> 18:31.611
After that, our friendship went south.

18:33.822 --> 18:36.240
I'm sorry about that.

18:39.036 --> 18:41.830
John, you don't have to be sorry.

18:42.956 --> 18:47.335
You were kids. You were scared.
You were trying to protect your dad.

18:48.127 --> 18:52.757
The problem was,
nobody was protecting your brother.

18:53.800 --> 18:57.178
Somebody needed to stand up for him.

18:57.387 --> 19:00.057
To tell the truth.

19:01.850 --> 19:03.852
I failed him.

19:04.644 --> 19:06.646
[♪♪♪]

19:14.821 --> 19:17.365
I looked up the case file.

19:19.367 --> 19:21.828
Read your transcripts.

19:24.122 --> 19:25.498
The tapes weren't there.

19:27.792 --> 19:31.546
I thought Danny
should hear the whole story.

19:41.848 --> 19:43.725
I was sorry to hear about your father.

19:43.934 --> 19:45.769
Thank you.

19:46.269 --> 19:49.689
I remember when he first hired me.
I was just 21.

19:49.898 --> 19:52.442
Yeah. I remember too.

19:52.650 --> 19:55.236
I had no experience. Nothing.

19:55.904 --> 19:58.489
And he took a chance on me.

19:59.282 --> 20:01.409
And then I let him down.

20:02.201 --> 20:03.954
Now I'm coming to you, like this.

20:05.496 --> 20:09.000
It's okay, Carlos. We should
talk about the charges against you.

20:09.876 --> 20:13.922
I pulled your file. The prosecution
is not going to make this easy.

20:14.131 --> 20:16.382
They're charging you
with larceny, robbery,

20:16.549 --> 20:18.885
and the knife
makes this aggravated assault.

20:19.094 --> 20:21.262
I had the knife on me,
but I didn't use it.

20:21.471 --> 20:25.391
That man owed me money,
and I was drinking, and I was drunk.

20:25.600 --> 20:26.726
And I lost my temper.

20:26.893 --> 20:28.394
[bell dings]

20:29.312 --> 20:31.022
I did this, but I didn't hurt anyone.

20:31.106 --> 20:33.524
It wasn't me,
it was the drinking and I've stopped.

20:33.733 --> 20:36.194
Yeah, he goes
to meetings every day now.

20:36.694 --> 20:38.655
That's good. That's an important step.

20:38.863 --> 20:44.119
I could show proof of the meetings.
I can take a test, blood, whatever.

20:44.327 --> 20:45.954
Did you tell the public defender?

20:46.163 --> 20:50.167
- He doesn't listen. He doesn't care.
- That's why we need you.

20:50.374 --> 20:54.629
I don't normally do this kind of thing.
I'm not a criminal defense attorney.

20:54.838 --> 20:57.841
But you know me. You care.

20:58.341 --> 20:59.676
Please, Ms. Rayburn.

21:00.551 --> 21:02.512
Will you take his case?

21:04.514 --> 21:06.891
I don't have nobody else to go to.

21:10.145 --> 21:11.980
- Mom?
- Hey, honey.

21:12.189 --> 21:15.859
- I'm trying to get in touch with--
- I'm gonna brighten up these cushions.

21:16.400 --> 21:20.030
Looks great. I'm trying to get with Danny.
Do you know where he is?

21:20.113 --> 21:22.782
No. He took a couple of days off.

21:24.909 --> 21:26.911
- For what?
- I don't know.

21:27.120 --> 21:31.958
But he didn't seem quite right,
so I thought it best to give him the time.

21:32.167 --> 21:36.462
- Mom, did he say where he was going?
- He mentioned Key West.

21:38.506 --> 21:41.926
Has he talked to you?
Is something going on with him?

21:42.135 --> 21:47.598
No. You know Danny.
Danny's Danny. Thank you.

21:48.683 --> 21:51.310
Mm. [clears throat]

21:52.729 --> 21:54.522
May I have another?

21:56.107 --> 21:59.318
[Tricia] You were in the other night.
I heard you all talking.

21:59.527 --> 22:01.529
Sorry about your loss.

22:02.239 --> 22:04.490
Don't be sorry.

22:10.163 --> 22:12.331
- This place is fucking dead.
- Ten bucks.

22:12.498 --> 22:14.000
Yeah.

22:16.711 --> 22:19.338
♪ You're a bad girl,
Yeah, I know that ♪

22:19.505 --> 22:21.883
♪ Like Rihanna, come on
I bet you show that ♪

22:22.050 --> 22:24.261
♪ You're a grown-up
We about to mix ♪

22:24.427 --> 22:26.179
♪ Party, don't you ever switch plans? ♪

22:26.345 --> 22:28.723
♪ It's the weekend
It ain't cheating if we chill ♪

