♪ Shorty about fun
I ain't messing with pretenders ♪

23:27.782 --> 23:30.118
♪ Party like a rock star
This life is for beginners ♪

23:30.327 --> 23:31.786
[woman]
You wanna go play?

23:32.078 --> 23:34.538
I think you might have something I want.

23:35.206 --> 23:36.415
What do you say?

23:38.501 --> 23:39.752
[woman chuckles]

23:40.295 --> 23:41.712
- Come on.
- Yeah.

23:42.255 --> 23:43.547
[Danny chuckles]

23:44.715 --> 23:45.758
♪ We ain't got to study, baby ♪

23:45.967 --> 23:48.136
♪ You can pass the class
I got a million-dollar question ♪♪

23:48.386 --> 23:50.554
Black '57 Chevy.

23:50.763 --> 23:55.643
Pickup truck. No, no. If you find it,
don't do anything. Just give me a call.

23:56.311 --> 23:59.814
Yeah. All right. All right. Thanks.

24:00.481 --> 24:04.861
So I was looking through some
old trafficking cases-- Are you okay?

24:06.029 --> 24:07.030
Yeah.

24:08.031 --> 24:10.325
Five years ago,
a ring was busted in Dade.

24:10.491 --> 24:13.619
They rescued a group of girls who
were coming from Central America.

24:13.828 --> 24:16.622
The rings leaders, they're all in jail.

24:16.831 --> 24:20.918
One of the girls said something
interesting in her statement right there.

24:21.127 --> 24:22.628
Her name is Cristina Colon.

24:23.587 --> 24:28.092
I tracked her down. She works up
in Homestead. Want me to run this?

24:28.551 --> 24:30.636
No, I got it.

24:30.928 --> 24:32.722
Okay.

24:33.681 --> 24:35.558
Thanks.

24:36.226 --> 24:38.686
The right judge,
I can get 7 to 10 with no parole.

24:38.895 --> 24:41.064
With only drunk
and disorderly in his priors?

24:41.272 --> 24:43.024
I don't understand what you're doing.

24:43.191 --> 24:46.361
- He isn't a hardened thug--
- You're not a criminal defense attorney.

24:46.569 --> 24:50.407
If you were, you'd understand that
what he's convicted of is only a fraction.

24:50.531 --> 24:54.077
- He used to do landscaping for my family.
- So you feel responsible for him.

24:54.244 --> 24:56.495
- It's personal.
- He just needs a little help.

24:56.704 --> 24:59.249
Okay. Stop. I've seen this movie.

24:59.457 --> 25:02.085
Don't defend this guy.
It isn't your thing.

25:02.293 --> 25:04.712
He has a drinking problem.
He isn't a bad guy.

25:04.921 --> 25:08.674
- So I let him off on agg robbery? Why?
- In trial, you never know.

25:08.883 --> 25:14.180
Karen, we're ready for fines,
community service, reparations,

25:14.389 --> 25:17.100
time already served.
But no new jail time.

25:19.102 --> 25:21.479
We'll call your office tomorrow
with our offer.

25:21.687 --> 25:23.147
But our only offer.

25:23.481 --> 25:24.482
Thank you.

25:24.941 --> 25:26.984
You won't love it.

25:48.506 --> 25:49.548
[clears throat]

25:49.715 --> 25:51.134
[car lock beeps]

25:52.718 --> 25:54.304
Hey there.

25:55.805 --> 25:56.847
Hi.

25:57.265 --> 25:59.558
I'm surprised to see you.

25:59.767 --> 26:02.228
I didn't know if you were still in town.

26:03.104 --> 26:05.648
Yeah. Looks like I am.
I had to get a mooring license.

26:05.856 --> 26:07.525
- Got a new boat.
- Nice.

26:08.276 --> 26:10.445
Thought I wasn't
supposed to be talking to you.

26:12.738 --> 26:14.907
[speaking in Spanish]

26:18.369 --> 26:21.456
Excuse me.
I'm looking for Cristina Colon?

26:21.664 --> 26:22.748
I'm Cristina.

26:22.957 --> 26:25.168
We spoke on the phone.
I'm Detective Rayburn.

26:25.376 --> 26:29.630
You're a detective?
I don't remember you.

26:29.839 --> 26:31.508
I didn't work your case.

26:31.715 --> 26:33.426
Then why do you want to talk to me?

26:33.634 --> 26:37.138
I'm investigating a different case.
I think you might be able to help me.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.183
Okay?

26:41.934 --> 26:46.689
When you and the girls were freed,
you gave a statement to authorities.

26:46.897 --> 26:49.484
- Yes.
- There was something in that statement

26:49.692 --> 26:51.944
that I'd like to talk to you about.

26:52.570 --> 26:53.946
Okay.

26:54.155 --> 26:58.409
When you were asked about
the men who brought you to the U.S.,

26:58.617 --> 27:02.455
you'd said that
"they threatened us with fire."

27:05.082 --> 27:09.837
They threatened us with everything
they could think. Every day.

27:10.046 --> 27:12.965
And this is when you were on the boat?

27:13.799 --> 27:15.801
Yes.

27:16.427 --> 27:18.513
How did they threaten you with fire?

27:20.723 --> 27:24.685
One night, the boat stopped.

27:25.353 --> 27:28.523
I think maybe
they saw the Coast Guard.

27:28.731 --> 27:32.276
So the men shut off the engines

27:32.443 --> 27:36.239
and told us not to make any noise.

27:36.739 --> 27:39.700
The girls were crying, and...

27:41.035 --> 27:44.705
the men got very angry.

27:47.208 --> 27:49.460
And...

27:51.254 --> 27:52.838
And...

27:54.382 --> 27:56.259
Just take your time. Please.

27:57.176 --> 27:58.302
I'm sorry.

27:58.761 --> 28:00.888
You don't need to be sorry.

28:09.813 --> 28:14.193
So they said if...

28:14.402 --> 28:20.991
we didn't stop crying,
they would lock us inside and burn us.

28:22.493 --> 28:28.124
And one man light a match
and he threw it down into the...

28:28.458 --> 28:30.293
[♪♪♪]

28:30.585 --> 28:32.795
- The hold?
- Yes.

28:33.003 --> 28:35.965
He threw the match in with us.

28:36.674 --> 28:38.008
It didn't do anything.

28:39.843 --> 28:42.012
Just one match.

28:44.181 --> 28:46.767
But after that, we knew.

28:46.976 --> 28:48.311
What did you know?

28:48.519 --> 28:52.356
That they would rather
burn us all alive than get caught.

28:58.529 --> 29:00.030
I owe you an apology.

29:00.114 --> 29:01.115
No, you don't.

29:01.198 --> 29:03.993
- You don't owe me anything.
- Yes, I do.

29:04.201 --> 29:06.870
It was really bad timing
and I overreacted.

29:07.079 --> 29:09.707
It's okay. I get it. Really.

29:13.711 --> 29:15.838
How are you holding up?

29:16.046 --> 29:19.467
I'm okay. You know, it's hard,

29:19.676 --> 29:21.844
but I'm better.

29:26.182 --> 29:29.393
So are you around now?
Are we talking again?

29:29.602 --> 29:32.062
No. I mean...

29:33.690 --> 29:37.610
- I've figured some things out.
- Good. That's good.

29:38.235 --> 29:42.573
Yeah. I have to stop acting like a child.

29:49.872 --> 29:53.543
Losing my father made me...

29:54.043 --> 29:57.547
Clarifies things, right?
It makes sense.

30:03.927 --> 30:06.723
- I'm sorry.
- Will you stop apologizing?

30:06.930 --> 30:08.432
Really.

30:10.267 --> 30:13.062
- Okay.
- Okay.

30:15.064 --> 30:19.276
Well, I'm glad
we bumped into each other.

30:19.443 --> 30:22.112
[laughs] Stop.

30:35.418 --> 30:37.836
[Latin dance music playing over speakers]

30:45.261 --> 30:47.388
[man]
First tour, I was 22 years old in Spain.

30:47.597 --> 30:50.974
Twenty-two in Spain?
I've never even left Florida.

30:51.267 --> 30:52.727
[Belle and man laughing]

30:52.935 --> 30:54.978
I've never been out of Florida.

30:55.187 --> 30:56.980
Oh, can I--

31:01.736 --> 31:04.321
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

31:05.489 --> 31:08.743
[Belle laughing]

31:21.464 --> 31:23.048
[Danny]
How'd you know I had some?

31:23.257 --> 31:27.136
[woman] Sucking the roof of your mouth,
bobbing your head off beat.

31:27.344 --> 31:28.929
I wasn't off beat.

31:29.096 --> 31:30.139
[sniffing]

31:30.389 --> 31:32.558
[woman]
You're too old for this bar.

31:32.725 --> 31:34.059
[door opens]

31:35.311 --> 31:37.438
It's cool. He's a friend.

31:38.021 --> 31:41.066
- [man] Hey.
- Hey.

31:41.275 --> 31:42.860
Can I hit it?

31:45.696 --> 31:49.492
The more the merrier. Sure, yeah.

31:49.659 --> 31:51.034
Get a little baby bit of that.

31:51.201 --> 31:52.202
[sniffing]

31:56.999 --> 31:58.125
[moaning]

31:58.292 --> 31:59.460
[man]
That's good.

32:00.169 --> 32:02.630
[techno music playing over speakers]

32:10.179 --> 32:11.597
[laughing]

32:25.944 --> 32:29.573
- Dad cut Danny out?
- [Meg] Yeah.

32:34.537 --> 32:37.456
- And when did this happen?
- Years ago.

32:37.832 --> 32:42.169
And before he died, I asked him if he
wanted to go through with it. He said yes.

32:43.253 --> 32:45.214
You just let Dad do this?

32:45.422 --> 32:49.719
I'm his lawyer.
My job is to carry out his wishes.

32:50.887 --> 32:54.598
Anyway, Mom's not happy about it.
She wants us to include Danny.

32:54.807 --> 32:57.601
Can she do that? Dad already decided.

32:57.810 --> 33:02.147
Well, the business is ours now. As long
as we all agree, we can do what we want.

33:02.356 --> 33:04.608
Does Danny know about this?

33:05.860 --> 33:08.445
- I don't think so.
- Easy decision. We cut him back in.

33:08.612 --> 33:12.783
Wait a minute. Just slow down one second.
Why would we do that?

33:12.991 --> 33:15.160
He's been through enough.
He doesn't need this.

33:15.369 --> 33:17.705
What do you mean
"he's been through enough"?

33:18.288 --> 33:21.291
All of it. His whole fucking childhood.
That's what I mean.

33:21.500 --> 33:23.001
What are you talking about?

33:24.127 --> 33:26.881
- You know what I'm fucking talking about.
- No, I don't.

33:30.050 --> 33:32.177
All right. You know what?

33:33.763 --> 33:34.931
[stammering]

33:35.013 --> 33:37.391
If you want to, do as you like.

33:37.600 --> 33:41.395
But if you cut Danny out,
just cut me out, too.

34:01.123 --> 34:03.793
- [man] We're out.
- Where to next?

34:04.001 --> 34:05.920
- [woman] Home. Mm.
- Mm.

34:06.086 --> 34:07.755
Where's that?

34:07.964 --> 34:10.257
You're sweet.

34:12.927 --> 34:15.178
See you around, buddy.

34:31.612 --> 34:33.948
Hey.

34:34.114 --> 34:35.866
Hey, whoa.

34:36.033 --> 34:38.577
[Tricia]
Oh, you're back.

34:39.161 --> 34:41.121
[rock music playing over speakers]

34:44.416 --> 34:46.293
[laughing]

34:49.922 --> 34:52.090
Come on, have a drink.
Have one with me.

34:52.299 --> 34:54.677
I don't drink. Not here.

34:55.093 --> 35:00.432
Wow. Surrounded by all these beautiful
bottles. I don't under-- I would be like

35:00.641 --> 35:02.685
fucking a--

35:03.686 --> 35:08.565
Fox in a hen house. Like a Cookie
Monster, and a-- What do you call it...

35:08.774 --> 35:11.527
A couple rum punches please.

35:18.534 --> 35:21.912
Are you in the Navy? Yeah?

35:24.081 --> 35:27.835
What's that? Is that a yes?

35:28.044 --> 35:30.170
Yes, like this.

35:30.379 --> 35:32.381
Hey, I'm talking to you, Navy guy.

35:33.883 --> 35:37.469
Well, I'm gonna do you a favor
and pretend you're not.

35:37.678 --> 35:39.096
- [Tricia] Two rum punches.
- Thanks.

35:39.304 --> 35:41.306
[laughing]
Rum punches?

35:42.224 --> 35:46.228
Wow. I bet you they don't let you
order that in the Navy, do they?

35:46.395 --> 35:50.315
Because they're kind of feminine,
you know. A bit of a woman's drink.

35:50.524 --> 35:53.318
Oh, that got his attention.

35:55.445 --> 35:56.780
You don't want to do this.

35:56.989 --> 36:01.535
Hey, buddy, I'm not the one
that's ordering a fucking rum punch.

36:02.119 --> 36:06.582
Look, why don't you do everybody a favor
and get your drunk ass off that stool,

36:06.790 --> 36:09.167
pay the lady, and leave?

36:11.169 --> 36:13.255
- Okay.
- Come on. Take it easy.

36:13.672 --> 36:17.384
I'm gonna leave. Okay?
I will leave. But can I try it?

36:17.593 --> 36:19.720
- Can I try it?
- Try what?

36:24.474 --> 36:26.518
You're kidding, right?

36:26.894 --> 36:28.353
[Danny]
Mm.

36:29.939 --> 36:31.398
Oh.

36:33.442 --> 36:38.614
It's kind of sweet.
A bit like a sailor's ass, isn't it?

36:38.781 --> 36:40.741
[Danny groans]

36:42.659 --> 36:44.327
[man]
You had enough?

36:44.954 --> 36:47.081
[woman]
Take it outside, guys.

36:48.540 --> 36:50.333
Oh, you got me good that time.

36:50.918 --> 36:52.878
Shit, man.

36:53.087 --> 36:56.632
Those sailor boys, they must
fucking love you, man. They must love--

36:57.591 --> 36:59.301
- Oh.
- [man 1] Come on.

37:00.094 --> 37:01.386
[grunting]

37:02.096 --> 37:04.014
[glasses shattering]

37:11.521 --> 37:13.983
- [chuckling]
- [woman] Come on, enough already.

37:14.942 --> 37:18.654
Hey, did I mention
that you should go fuck yourself?

37:18.862 --> 37:24.660
Because I think you should
go fuck your own self, buddy.

37:31.000 --> 37:33.085
Is this what you wanted?

37:34.252 --> 37:36.254
[♪♪♪]

37:39.341 --> 37:40.968
You had enough?

37:52.395 --> 37:55.398
Fuck, fuck. Let's just do this.

37:59.236 --> 38:00.821
Hey.

38:02.280 --> 38:04.241
- Hi.
- Hey, are you okay?

38:04.449 --> 38:07.786
Yeah, I'm good. I'm okay.
How are you?

38:08.537 --> 38:10.455
Same. What's going on?

38:10.664 --> 38:13.000
I just-- I wanted to give you these.

38:13.209 --> 38:17.546
These are yours now,
and I really shouldn't have them anymore.

38:18.255 --> 38:19.715
So, okay.

38:20.423 --> 38:23.886
And listen,
I just wanted to say that

38:24.053 --> 38:27.639
I know that I've been
a little slow on the uptake,

38:27.848 --> 38:29.599
and it's taken me a little while,

38:29.683 --> 38:34.021
but I just want to let you know
that I get it.

38:35.189 --> 38:38.901
I do get it. And I'm okay.

38:41.611 --> 38:43.405
Thank you.

38:45.074 --> 38:47.576
And, uh...

38:48.493 --> 38:50.037
And I love you.

38:53.290 --> 38:56.210
And I'm always gonna love you, so...

38:57.002 --> 39:01.090
you know... That's the deal.

39:05.343 --> 39:08.097
- So...
- I love you, too.

39:08.305 --> 39:09.514
I do.

39:12.434 --> 39:15.229
All right. So okay.

39:16.813 --> 39:19.066
- I need my car key.
- Oh.

39:19.399 --> 39:20.442
[laughing]

39:20.609 --> 39:24.321
- Yeah. Smooth.
- You're not gonna get far without it.

39:25.281 --> 39:26.782
I know.

39:33.747 --> 39:35.373
[urinating]

39:35.999 --> 39:39.128
Who the fuck is that?

39:43.006 --> 39:44.133
Jesus, Danny.

39:45.342 --> 39:47.594
What the fuck are you doing here?

39:47.803 --> 39:49.096
Tricia called me.

39:49.305 --> 39:50.931
Who's Tricia?

39:51.807 --> 39:55.060
The bartender. She thinks someone
should take you home.

39:55.269 --> 39:58.021
- No.
- I got you. Let me take you home.

39:58.230 --> 39:59.815
Come on, Danny. Get in the car.

40:00.023 --> 40:03.026
Fuck off, man. Fuck off me.

40:04.361 --> 40:06.571
Danny, you need help right now.
Come on.

40:06.780 --> 40:08.865
Why? Because you care?

40:09.074 --> 40:12.869
- Danny, I do care. Get in the car.
- Let me tell you something.

40:14.121 --> 40:17.124
I'm not your way out.
I'm not your fucking lifeline.

40:18.959 --> 40:22.671
And you sure as shit are not mine.

40:22.879 --> 40:24.840
- Yeah, no shit.
- Okay?

40:25.924 --> 40:28.010
So let me make
this nice and simple for you.

40:28.177 --> 40:32.555
Now's the time you say, "Fuck off,"
I say to you "Fuck off," and we're done.

40:33.974 --> 40:35.392
Okay? Say it.

40:36.185 --> 40:37.894
Say it.

40:40.272 --> 40:44.901
Say it! Don't want to play
the fuck off game? Okay, try this.

40:45.110 --> 40:47.237
I don't care about you.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.406
You don't mean anything to me.

40:49.614 --> 40:54.411
And if I mean something to you,

40:54.577 --> 41:00.000
you mean less than nothing to me.

41:01.835 --> 41:02.919
Why are you doing this?

41:05.381 --> 41:07.799
This is what I do.

41:18.977 --> 41:20.979
[♪♪♪]

42:00.727 --> 42:02.145
Where you headed, man?

42:05.148 --> 42:08.151
Hey, man. Can I come with you?

42:08.360 --> 42:10.779
Yeah, come on.

42:10.946 --> 42:12.614
I'll take you somewhere.

42:12.781 --> 42:14.199
[rap music playing over car stereo]

42:14.366 --> 42:15.451
- Need help?
- No.

42:15.658 --> 42:17.244
You got it?

42:17.702 --> 42:20.163
Oh, look at you.

42:21.039 --> 42:22.832
You're having fun tonight.

42:23.041 --> 42:24.876
Yeah, it's good, brother.

42:25.085 --> 42:28.255
- Yeah? Okay.
- Yeah, I'm good to go. Let's bounce.

42:29.339 --> 42:31.216
Let's go.

42:31.800 --> 42:34.010
- Safety first, right?
- Always.

42:34.177 --> 42:35.220
[both laugh]

42:35.387 --> 42:38.640
Oh, man. I'm so glad I met you.

42:55.449 --> 42:57.493
- Thanks for the call.
- No problem.

42:57.700 --> 42:59.453
- Borrow your light?
- Sure.

43:21.224 --> 43:23.226
[♪♪♪]

43:43.038 --> 43:45.874
[dogs barking]

43:47.959 --> 43:50.170
[rock music playing over speakers]

43:50.628 --> 43:52.964
♪ To make records with a mobile ♪

43:53.131 --> 43:55.050
[barking]

43:55.258 --> 43:58.470
♪ We didn't have much time ♪

43:58.636 --> 44:01.723
♪ Frank Zappa and the Mothers ♪

44:01.890 --> 44:05.685
♪ Were at the best place around ♪

44:06.019 --> 44:07.770
Hey.

44:09.189 --> 44:12.859
♪ Burned the place to the ground ♪

44:13.026 --> 44:14.570
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

44:14.777 --> 44:16.279
[woman]
Here.

44:16.696 --> 44:19.032
Take it. Go on.

44:20.534 --> 44:24.704
♪ Smoke on the water ♪

44:26.748 --> 44:28.083
[Danny coughs]

44:29.876 --> 44:31.753
[Babyface]
Just like that.

44:31.961 --> 44:33.338
Just...

44:33.547 --> 44:35.173
like that.

44:35.424 --> 44:37.467
[coughing]

44:38.218 --> 44:39.553
[Babyface laughing]

44:39.719 --> 44:41.804
What's in this?

44:42.013 --> 44:47.310
Some shit... that'll do... the trick.

44:48.770 --> 44:50.730
That'll work.

44:51.940 --> 44:53.775
[Babyface]
Just light it.

44:55.360 --> 44:58.280
♪ When it all was over ♪

44:58.863 --> 45:01.491
♪ We had to find another place ♪

45:03.243 --> 45:04.661
[sniffs then coughs]

45:07.414 --> 45:08.957
[inhales deeply]

45:11.126 --> 45:12.877
[engines revving, tires screeching]

45:13.253 --> 45:14.879
[cop 1]
Everybody freeze right now!

45:15.046 --> 45:16.298
[dogs barking and sirens wailing]

45:16.465 --> 45:19.342
- [cop 2] Get your hands up!
- [cop 3] Nobody move!

45:19.926 --> 45:22.679
[cop 2] Get your hands up!
Up where I can see them!

45:22.845 --> 45:25.974
- [cop 3] Hands up, right now!
- [cop 2] Don't you move!

45:27.058 --> 45:28.435
[Danny grunts]

45:28.602 --> 45:30.437
What are you doing?

45:36.401 --> 45:39.362
- [John] What the fuck are you doing?
- I'm having a little bit of fun!

45:39.446 --> 45:41.281
The fucking position you put us in?

45:41.657 --> 45:45.702
- If anyone finds out about this--
- It would reflect badly on the family.

45:45.910 --> 45:49.164
Is that what you're fucking worried about?
Except Dad's dead,

45:49.372 --> 45:52.083
so I don't think
it's going to affect him too much.

45:52.292 --> 45:54.377
What the fuck is that?
Some kind of excuse?

45:54.586 --> 45:56.796
No, man. That's not an excuse.

45:57.005 --> 45:58.881
That's your fucking excuse.

45:58.965 --> 46:02.260
Oh, you're going to protect Daddy
at all costs.

46:02.469 --> 46:06.556
Is that what this is about? You're feeling
fucking sorry for yourself because you

46:06.723 --> 46:11.102
found out someone told fibs a long time
ago about what Dad did to you? Is that it?

46:11.311 --> 46:14.314
Well, let me fucking clear
up some fucking things for you.

46:14.523 --> 46:16.816
Let me give you the truth.
We didn't lie for Dad.

46:17.025 --> 46:18.985
We fucking lied for you.

46:19.486 --> 46:23.781
Know why we lied? If they didn't shut it
down the cops would have kept pushing,

46:23.948 --> 46:26.868
and pushing, until they
start investigating Sarah's death.

46:27.035 --> 46:28.828
What do you think about that, asshole?

46:29.037 --> 46:30.997
There was nothing to investigate.

46:31.206 --> 46:33.542
You really think just because
you didn't mean for her to die

46:33.709 --> 46:37.587
- you weren't responsible?
- Fuck you. It was an accident.

46:37.795 --> 46:40.923
Why don't you quit fucking lying
to yourself, Danny?

46:41.924 --> 46:43.635
What did you say?

46:43.843 --> 46:45.387
I'm fucking taking you in.

46:45.721 --> 46:48.557
Fuck! Fuck! Ah!

46:50.433 --> 46:52.728
- What did you fucking say?
- Easy.

46:54.020 --> 46:55.188
Easy.

46:55.731 --> 46:57.148
Easy.

46:58.775 --> 46:59.942
Who the fuck is that?

47:02.320 --> 47:03.821
She's with me.

47:04.906 --> 47:06.908
She's been with me
the whole fucking time.

47:07.409 --> 47:09.411
[♪♪♪]

47:13.749 --> 47:16.376
[woman]
Are you sure you want to do this?

47:16.585 --> 47:18.211
Listen to her.

47:20.296 --> 47:22.257
Listen to her, Danny.

47:22.799 --> 47:24.384
[woman]
Don't screw this up.

47:25.719 --> 47:27.596
Give me the gun, Danny.

47:34.102 --> 47:35.562
Danny.

47:37.689 --> 47:39.274
[woman]
Time to decide.

47:43.319 --> 47:46.740
Is it you? Or is it them?

47:51.745 --> 47:54.790
Fucking listen to her. Danny?

47:54.997 --> 47:56.332
[grunts]

47:59.795 --> 48:01.129
Danny.

48:01.546 --> 48:03.047
Give me the gun, Danny.

48:03.715 --> 48:07.510
- Don't do that. Give me the fucking gun.
- [woman] Is it you? Or is it them?

48:07.803 --> 48:09.262
Shut up!

48:22.484 --> 48:25.403
♪ Smoke on the water ♪♪

48:25.528 --> 48:26.780
[laughter]

48:39.292 --> 48:45.590
♪ We'll turn it up, we'll pick up speed
Oh, we can ♪

48:45.757 --> 48:47.467
What?

48:49.636 --> 48:51.638
What's up with you, huh?

48:56.351 --> 48:57.644
Marco Diaz.

48:58.269 --> 49:00.062
Did you know...

49:00.271 --> 49:04.484
if you scramble the letters
of your name, it spells ZODIAC RAM?

49:04.693 --> 49:05.735
And you're an Aries.

49:07.403 --> 49:10.782
- I didn't realize that.
- And I'm a Virgo.

49:10.990 --> 49:14.911
And that the letters
of my name scrambled...

49:16.120 --> 49:19.457
make "Mrs. Marco Diaz."

49:23.378 --> 49:25.755
What's going on with you today?

49:31.052 --> 49:32.428
[Meg]
Oops.

49:34.389 --> 49:38.142
Can you pick that up for me?
Please?

49:42.438 --> 49:44.858
Come on. Pick it up.

49:47.777 --> 49:49.070
Ask me.

49:49.571 --> 49:53.115
Get on one knee, and ask me.

49:57.370 --> 49:59.414
You want me to propose to you?

50:01.082 --> 50:02.834
You want me to do it?

50:12.260 --> 50:13.762
[fork clangs]

50:18.266 --> 50:22.562
♪ And love leads to each others' arms ♪

50:22.687 --> 50:26.608
♪ That first kiss underneath the stars ♪♪

50:26.775 --> 50:28.777
I don't think you're ready.

50:32.948 --> 50:34.783
I'm sorry.

50:39.370 --> 50:41.581
[woman]
Yeah, I suppose. I mean, if you want to.

50:41.790 --> 50:45.919
Help me, Rhonda. Two fingers.

50:46.127 --> 50:47.712
Thank you.

50:51.925 --> 50:53.885
Oh, hey. Morning.

50:54.093 --> 50:55.637
Hey.

50:56.638 --> 50:59.474
I see you're still celebrating.

51:00.767 --> 51:02.059
Oh, yeah.

51:02.226 --> 51:03.519
[both laughing]

51:03.770 --> 51:07.732
- Your freedom.
- Yeah, my freedom.

51:07.941 --> 51:10.401
- Sorry about that.
- No worries.

51:10.610 --> 51:13.989
No. I'm-- You know what?
I am. I am celebrating.

51:14.155 --> 51:17.074
I'm celebrating that this is
the greatest country in the world.

51:17.241 --> 51:19.535
Guess how much
it costs to get a divorce online?

51:20.328 --> 51:22.163
- I don't know.
- Just take a gander.

51:22.371 --> 51:23.832
No idea.

51:24.040 --> 51:25.750
Just take a guess.

51:25.959 --> 51:28.044
Throw out a number.
Tell you what,

51:28.210 --> 51:31.297
you come within 20 bucks
and I'll buy you a drink.

51:32.298 --> 51:33.967
Uh...

51:34.592 --> 51:37.470
- Two hundred dollars?
- Ehh. One hundred fifty-nine.

51:37.679 --> 51:42.099
Close enough, you can still have your
drink. And you can do it under an hour.

51:42.308 --> 51:45.770
Who knew? What are you drinking?
Anything you want.

51:46.062 --> 51:47.522
- This is my lucky day.
- Right.

51:47.647 --> 51:49.148
- I never win anything.
- Well...

51:49.732 --> 51:51.067
Um...

51:51.275 --> 51:54.779
- Obviously, nothing imported.
- Obviously.

51:54.988 --> 52:00.284
And it also has to be a beer, in a can.
But, you know. [chuckles]

52:02.370 --> 52:05.581
Um... Can I ask you something?

52:05.790 --> 52:09.836
Are you and, um, ahem, my brother...

52:12.296 --> 52:13.506
I don't know.

52:16.634 --> 52:18.011
Okay.

52:21.931 --> 52:23.933
You know what?
I'll have what you're having.

52:24.141 --> 52:25.309
Sounds good.

53:04.057 --> 53:05.558
Back to work, huh?

53:05.767 --> 53:08.061
Oh, yeah.

53:08.269 --> 53:10.438
The guests
caught a couple of snapper.

53:10.605 --> 53:13.399
I'm going to prepare them,
then grill them up.

53:13.608 --> 53:15.568
Mom said you were
taking a few days off.

53:17.403 --> 53:21.032
I drove down to Key West for a day.
That'll do.

53:24.243 --> 53:25.327
Found your truck.

53:30.207 --> 53:31.250
It was out of gas.

53:40.426 --> 53:42.053
I know you talked to Lenny Potts.

53:45.765 --> 53:47.934
Yeah. Well, he came to me.

53:48.143 --> 53:50.394
- I spoke to him.
- Mm-hm.

53:52.480 --> 53:53.648
Maybe we should talk.

54:03.741 --> 54:05.409
All right.

54:07.411 --> 54:09.080
Talk.

54:14.961 --> 54:17.296
What Dad did was wrong.

54:21.258 --> 54:23.469
I couldn't see clearly back then.

54:24.762 --> 54:27.890
I just wanted the whole fucking thing
to be over with.

54:30.059 --> 54:33.021
Everyone was just trying
to hold everything together.

54:34.355 --> 54:37.150
I said what I thought I had to say.

54:38.609 --> 54:40.444
I was wrong.

54:46.367 --> 54:48.661
We were all fucking wrong.

55:00.715 --> 55:03.218
Now that Dad's gone...

55:06.762 --> 55:09.265
Fucking I don't know.
I don't know.

55:11.142 --> 55:12.810
I'd like to start over.

55:19.150 --> 55:21.569
So you still want to go fishing?

55:22.486 --> 55:24.280
What?

55:26.115 --> 55:29.785
You don't remember? The other night
you asked me, you wanted to go fishing.

55:29.994 --> 55:32.163
Still want to go fishing?

55:34.665 --> 55:35.958
Yeah, I want to go fishing.

55:40.255 --> 55:43.091
You know, you don't have to
worry about me, John.

55:44.175 --> 55:45.634
I mean...

55:46.761 --> 55:49.805
You got your own family to worry about.

55:51.766 --> 55:53.475
Just want to be able to get past all this.

55:53.893 --> 55:56.437
We are past it.

55:56.645 --> 55:58.606
It's passed.

56:05.113 --> 56:06.739
It's good to have you home.

56:08.241 --> 56:10.952
It's so good to be back.

56:32.181 --> 56:33.724
[exhales]

56:36.644 --> 56:38.104
[laughs]

56:51.700 --> 56:53.786
[♪♪♪]
